node.title: Head in, Khawaja misses out — Australia names its XI for the first Ashes Test
node.alt: Two smiling Australian cricketers walk onto Adelaide Oval to field in a Test match wearing their Baggy Greens.
node.description: Australia finalises its Test team for the opening match of the Ashes series at the Gabba, with Travis Head getting the nod ahead of Usman Khawaja to bat at number five against England.
node.content: ["Australia has named its team for the first Ashes Test against England at the\u00a0Gabba, with South Australia's Travis Head preferred for the last batting spot ahead of Queensland veteran Usman Khawaja.", "Selectors had\u00a0already confirmed that Alex Carey would be Australia's wicketkeeper for the Gabba, replacing former skipper Tim Paine.", "Australian XI:\u00a0 David Warner, Marcus Harris, Marnus Labuschagne, Steve Smith, Travis Head, Cameron Green, Alex Carey, Pat Cummins (capt), Nathan Lyon, Josh Hazlewood, Mitchell Starc.", "More to come."]
